Text: This past week has seen a lot of progress in development.
I have enjoyed learning about wordpress, although I do find it very clunky and difficult to customise.
I think I would enjoy the experience more if we were able to purchase some key plugins to make the site more customisable.
With that being said, everything I have needed to do I have been able to make happen through watching YouTube tutorials and essentially bootstrapping the process.
There are a lot of videos which explain how to achieve the desired outcomes by simply adding a few lines of code and customising specific things.
I was tasked with the job of putting all our work together.
This has been a lot of fun and I have learnt so much about website design.
This has enabled me to learn about a very key development skill and has helped me find my stride where, at times, I have not been confident in my development skills.
Kiki has taken on the role of organising the usability test which has been great due to my lack in understanding of this process.
She has done a lot of reading regarding the process of the usability test and used Teacher1â€™s research as an example of how to achieve the usability test.
This is our main task to achieve in this upcoming week.
This final week is important for us to wrap up what we have done and package the work we have done in an easily accessible way.
This has been somewhat my job with merging all our work together.
I think the obstacles for the next week is time.
We all have a lot on our plates at the moment, so getting the website packaged will be an interesting process.
It is pivotal we do this well as it makes it more likely that our website will be deployed and used to replace the OPTâ€™s current website.
I plan to overcome this by continuing my work of merging everything and utilizing free education resources such as YouTube to learn what I need to in order to achieve the end result.
I also plan to iterate on the website as we go forward with the usability test in order to action the feedback we are receiving regarding design and functionality changes it requires.
This will ensure changes are made as the project wraps up and ensures our design is fit for purpose and operational.
Overall, I.  have found our budget to be a barrier for us regarding achieving the desired functionalities we wish to.
Another barrier has been merging multiple team members different work onto the website as all plugins have to be developed so differently.
Consistency in design is important and I have not been able to keep the design language clear and concise from page to page which is another one of my roles this next week.
